This is the most important concept in modern AI. Attention is what separates transformers from everything that came before — it lets every token "look at" every other token simultaneously and decide what's relevant.
The core idea is simple:

When processing a word, instead of reading left-to-right one word at a time, ask: which other words in this sentence should I pay attention to right now?

For example, in "The animal didn't cross the street because it was too tired" — what does "it" refer to? A human instantly knows it's "animal". Attention teaches the model to make that same connection.
