The key insight about training
Every training step asks the same question: given these tokens so far, what comes next? The model sees "the cat sat on the" and must predict "mat". When it's wrong, the loss is high. Backpropagation sends a signal backward through all the weights — attention matrices, FFN, embeddings — nudging each one in the direction that reduces the error. Do this billions of times and the weights encode everything the model "knows."
